('B2',2,'essay','formal_email','Write a 4-sentence complaint email to a company.',NULL,'I am writing to express my dissatisfaction with your service. The product arrived damaged despite careful handling. I would appreciate a full refund at your earliest convenience. I trust this matter will be resolved promptly.','Use formal register and appropriate phrases.','formal complaint patterns.',120),
('B2',2,'essay','argument','Argue for or against online learning (4 sentences).',NULL,'While online learning offers flexibility, it lacks human interaction. On one hand, students can study at their own pace. On the other hand, motivation becomes a challenge. Overall, a hybrid approach seems optimal.','Use discourse markers.','on one hand/other hand, overall.',120),
('B2',2,'essay','cleft_emphasis','Emphasize different elements (4 cleft sentences).',NULL,'What surprises me most is his honesty. It was the team that made the difference. The thing I value most is time. It is determination that leads to success.','Use what- and it-clefts.','cleft for emphasis.',120),
('B2',2,'essay','inversion_style','Write 4 sentences with inversion in formal style.',NULL,'Little did they know about the changes. Never before have I faced such a challenge. Only by hard work can we succeed. Seldom does she miss a deadline.','Use various inversions.','little/never/only/seldom inversions.',120),
('B2',2,'essay','mixed_conditional_regrets','Describe 4 mixed regrets.',NULL,'If I had saved more, I would be wealthier today. If I were not so shy, I would have made more friends. If he had listened to advice, he would not be in trouble now. If she spoke English, she would have got that job.','Mix past and present in conditionals.','past perfect + would + base (present); were + would have + part.',120),
('B2',2,'essay','subjunctive_usage','Write 4 sentences using subjunctive after suggest, insist, recommend, essential.',NULL,'The manager suggested that we arrive early. She insisted that he apologize. I recommend that the report be revised. It is essential that everyone attend the meeting.','Use base form in subjunctive.','bare infinitive after mandative verbs.',120),
('B2',2,'essay','advanced_passive','Rewrite 4 sentences using reporting passives.',NULL,'The minister is thought to have lied. The company is said to be in trouble. The treaty is believed to have failed. The drug is reported to cause side effects.','Use is thought/said/believed/reported.','reporting structures with passive.',120),
('B2',2,'essay','idioms_register','Use 4 idioms appropriately in sentences.',NULL,'That test was a piece of cake. She is under the weather today. He let the cat out of the bag. We are in the same boat.','Use idioms with correct context.','common English idioms.',120),
