('C1',2,'essay','nominalization','Rewrite 4 sentences using nominalization.',NULL,'The deterioration of infrastructure is alarming. The expansion of services is underway. The rejection of the proposal surprised many. The reorganization of the department was successful.','Use abstract nouns.','deteriorate -> deterioration.',120),
('C1',2,'essay','complex_syntax','Write 4 sentences with complex structures.',NULL,'Not only did the strategy succeed, but it also exceeded expectations. Were this approach adopted, substantial savings would follow. Scarcely had the report been released when it was criticized. Such was the public outcry that policy changed.','Use inversions and complex forms.','not only, were, scarcely, such was.',120),
('C1',2,'essay','academic_register','Write 4 sentences with academic register.',NULL,'The present study investigates the implications of the proposed reform. Our findings align with prior research, yet diverge in key respects. These outcomes warrant further investigation. We therefore recommend a comprehensive review.','Use formal academic style.','investigates, align, diverge, warrant.',120),
('C1',2,'essay','reported_speech_advanced','Use 4 advanced reporting structures.',NULL,'She is reported to have accepted the position. He is alleged to have falsified the records. The committee is understood to be divided. The minister is believed to have resigned.','Use passive reporting.','is reported/alleged/understood/believed.',120),
('C1',2,'essay','cleft_advanced','Use 4 advanced cleft structures.',NULL,'It was her unwavering commitment that inspired the team. What proved decisive was the timing of the announcement. The very essence of the argument is its simplicity. All that remains is to ratify the agreement.','Use varied clefts.','it was, what, the very, all that.',120),
('C1',2,'essay','formal_letter','Write 4 sentences of a formal business letter.',NULL,'I trust this letter finds you well. I am writing to propose a partnership between our organizations. Should this proposal be of interest, I would welcome a meeting. I look forward to your considered response.','Use formal business style.','trust, propose, should, welcome.',120),
