('C2',1,'essay','literary_analysis','Write a 4-sentence literary analysis of a novel.',NULL,'The novels fractured chronology mirrors the protagonists disintegrating psyche. Time itself becomes a character, elusive and unreliable. The authors spare prose belies the emotional weight of each scene. Ultimately, the work interrogates the very nature of memory.','Use literary vocabulary.','fractured, disintegrating, elusive, interrogate.',120),
('C2',1,'essay','philosophical','Discuss a philosophical concept in 4 sentences.',NULL,'Free will, as traditionally conceived, presupposes an agent capable of alternative actions. Yet determinism challenges this presupposition at its root. The compatibilist response seeks to reconcile the two, though not without residual difficulties. The debate, far from settled, continues to generate sophisticated argumentation.','Use philosophical register.','presuppose, reconcile, residual, generate.',120),
('C2',1,'essay','rhetorical','Write a 4-sentence rhetorically rich passage.',NULL,'We stand not at the end of an era, but at its rebirth. We have been tested, we have been divided, yet we have endured. Let us remember, then, not what divides but what unites. For in unity lies not merely strength, but purpose.','Use rhetorical devices.','anaphora, antithesis, inversion.',120),
('C2',1,'essay','nuanced_opinion','Write a nuanced 4-sentence opinion.',NULL,'While recent reforms have been widely celebrated, their long-term implications remain uncertain. The measures address symptoms rather than causes, a distinction often overlooked. To dismiss them as inadequate, however, would be both unfair and unhelpful. What is needed, rather, is a reasoned assessment informed by evidence.','Express nuanced positions.','remain uncertain, distinction, unhelpful.',120),
('C2',1,'essay','stylistic','Write 4 sentences demonstrating stylistic variety.',NULL,'She paused. Then, with a composure she did not feel, she began to speak. Words came haltingly at first, then in a torrent, then not at all. The silence that followed was, in its way, the most eloquent speech of all.','Vary sentence length and rhythm.','stylistic variation for effect.',120),
('C2',1,'essay','connotation','Use 4 words with precise connotations.',NULL,'He delivered a blistering critique of the proposal. Her manner was disarmingly candid. The room fell into a pregnant silence. His concession was both reluctant and magnanimous.','Use words with strong connotation.','blistering, disarming, pregnant, magnanimous.',120),
('C2',1,'essay','ambiguity','Craft 4 deliberately ambiguous sentences.',NULL,'She decided, in the end, to go. He said nothing, and that said everything. The truth, if that is what it was, came later. They left together, though not, perhaps, in the same direction.','Use ambiguity artistically.','deliberate open interpretation.',120),
('C2',1,'essay','register','Write 4 sentences in elevated literary register.',NULL,'The afternoon light fell obliquely across the marble floor, rendering familiar objects strange. From the garden came the desultory song of a solitary bird. She sat motionless, as if any motion might shatter the fragile calm. Time, it seemed, had quietly withdrawn from the room.','Use literary register.','obliquely, desultory, motionless, fragile.',120),
