('C2',2,'essay','analytical','Analyze a cultural phenomenon in 4 sentences.',NULL,'The phenomenon defies straightforward classification, resisting the categories typically invoked. It emerges at the confluence of economic, technological, and cultural currents, each exerting its own pressure. To treat any single dimension as primary would be to impoverish the analysis. What is required, rather, is an account capable of honouring the phenomenons constitutive complexity.','Use advanced analytical language.','confluence, exert, impoverish, constitutive.',120),
('C2',2,'essay','rhetorical','Compose a rhetorically crafted 4-sentence passage.',NULL,'We inherit a world we did not make, and which we are charged to remake. We did not choose the burdens of history, yet we must bear them. But we can, if we will it, choose the future. And in that choosing lies our freedom, our responsibility, our hope.','Use rhetorical devices.','anaphora, chiasmus, tricolon.',120),
('C2',2,'essay','philosophical','Argue a philosophical position (4 sentences).',NULL,'To suppose that meaning inheres in the text alone is to neglect the readers constitutive role. Interpretation is not a passive recovery but an active co-production. This is not to surrender to relativism; interpretations remain answerable to evidence. Rather, it is to acknowledge that meaning is relational and historically situated.','Use philosophical rigor.','inhere, constitutive, surrender, relational.',120),
('C2',2,'essay','literary_review','Review a novel (4 sentences).',NULL,'This is a novel of quiet devastation, its power lying less in what happens than in what is withheld. The prose moves with a lapidary precision, each sentence weighted and unhurried. The characters, for all their specificity, seem to stand for something larger than themselves. It is, in the end, a book about the slow accumulation of loss.','Use literary critical register.','lapidary, withheld, accumulation.',120),
('C2',2,'essay','nuanced','Write 4 sentences with nuanced qualification.',NULL,'The argument, though compelling in its broad strokes, falters in the detail. There is much here to admire; there is equally much to contest. To call the project a failure would be both inaccurate and ungenerous; to call it a success would be premature. Perhaps, in the end, these binaries do less work than we imagine.','Qualify claims precisely.','broad strokes, falter, contest, premature.',120),
('C2',2,'essay','aphoristic','Write 4 aphoristic sentences.',NULL,'Power, unexamined, corrupts quietly. Truth is seldom as pure as those who claim it. We distrust most those whose virtues mirror our failures. The future, like the past, will be misremembered.','Craft memorable concise statements.','aphoristic compression.',120),
('C2',2,'essay','essay_intro','Write an essay introduction (4 sentences).',NULL,'Few concepts are at once so familiar and so elusive as that of identity. Invoked daily in contexts from the political to the intimate, it resists the very coherence it purports to confer. This essay sets out to map the fault lines of that paradox. It argues that identity is best understood not as an essence but as a practice.','Use essayistic style.','familiar, elusive, fault lines, practice.',120),
('C2',2,'essay','ironic','Write 4 sentences employing irony.',NULL,'It is, of course, a remarkable coincidence that the committees findings so exactly accord with the preferences of those who appointed it. We are assured that this is mere accident. One is reassured, naturally, by the gravity with which this assurance is offered. Whether the public will share this reassurance is another matter entirely.','Use sustained irony.','sustained ironic register.',120),
